ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: Named locations of or within the body.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.

Concepts.definition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The large vein that carries blood from the head, neck, arms, and chest to the heart.

Concepts.definition: The large vein that terminates in the right atrium and transports deoxygenated blood from the head, neck, arms, and chest to the heart.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: In anatomy indicating higher than a given reference point.: A branch of the abdominal aorta that supplies blood to the intestines.

Concepts.definition: In anatomy, indicating higher than a given reference point.
A branch of the abdominal aorta that supplies blood to the intestines.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The continuation of the axillary vein which follows the subclavian artery and then joins the internal jugular vein to form the brachiocephalic vein.: Either of two veins including the right and left innominate vein.: A blood vessel that carries blood toward the heart.

Concepts.definition: The vein that drains the axillary vein and joins the internal jugular vein to form the brachiocephalic vein. The subclavian vein runs parallel to the subclavian artery.
Either of two veins including the right and left innominate vein.
A blood vessel that carries blood toward the heart.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An artery located below the clavicle that supplies blood to the head and the arms. The right subclavian artery originates from the brachiocephalic artery and the left subclavian artery originates from the aortic arch.: An artery of the mediastinum; in general it arises from the aortic arch and branches to form the right subclavian artery and one or both common carotid arteries.: A blood vessel that carries blood away from the heart.

Concepts.definition: An artery located below the clavicle that supplies blood to the head and the arms. The right subclavian artery originates from the brachiocephalic artery and the left subclavian artery originates from the aortic arch.
An artery arising from the aortic arch that divides into the right common carotid and right subclavian arteries.
A blood vessel that carries blood away from the heart.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The veins which return blood from the kidneys to the vena cava.

Concepts.definition: The veins which return blood from the kidneys to the vena cava.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Either of two arteries (right or left) that arise from the aorta to supply the kidneys.

Concepts.definition: Either of two arteries (right or left) that arise from the aorta to supply the kidneys.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Of or pertaining to a porta, especially the porta of the liver; as, the portal vein, which enters the liver at the porta, and divides into capillaries after the manner of an artery. Portal is applied to other veins which break up into capillaries; as, the renal portal veins in the frog.: A blood vessel that carries blood toward the heart.

Concepts.definition: Of or pertaining to a porta, especially the porta of the liver; as, the portal vein, which enters the liver at the porta, and divides into capillaries after the manner of an artery. Portal is applied to other veins which break up into capillaries; as, the renal portal veins in the frog.
A blood vessel that carries blood toward the heart.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A large vein that empties into the heart. It carries blood from the legs and feet and from organs in the abdomen and pelvis.

Concepts.definition: A large vein that returns blood from the lower half of the body to the heart.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A vein on either side of the body which is formed by the union of the external and internal iliac veins and passes upward to join with its fellow of the opposite side to form the inferior vena cava.

Concepts.definition: Any of the three veins including the common, external and internal iliac veins.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A branch of the abdominal aorta that supplies blood to the lower trunk and the legs.

Concepts.definition: A branch of the abdominal aorta that supplies blood to the lower trunk and the legs.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A straight line through a body or figure that satisfies certain conditions.: A major abdominal artery that arises from the abdominal aorta below the diaphragm.  It supplies blood to the digestive organs. It has three major branches, left gastric artery, common hepatic artery, and splenic artery.

Concepts.definition: A straight line through a body or figure that satisfies certain conditions.

A major abdominal artery that arises from the abdominal aorta below the diaphragm.  It supplies blood to the digestive organs. It has three major branches, left gastric artery, common hepatic artery, and splenic artery.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The major arterial trunk that carries oxygenated blood from the left ventricle into the ascending aorta behind the heart, the aortic arch, through the thorax as the descending aorta and through the abdomen as the abdominal aorta; it bifurcates into the left and right common iliac arteries.

Concepts.definition: The major arterial trunk that carries oxygenated blood from the left ventricle into the ascending aorta behind the heart, the aortic arch, through the thorax as the descending aorta and through the abdomen as the abdominal aorta; it bifurcates into the left and right common iliac arteries.
